56.5	Asado	Asado	In Chile, the local version (whole roast lamb) is usually accompanied with , a local condiment made from pureed herbs, garlic, and hot peppers; in many ways similar to . The dish is typical of southern Chile and is served hot accompanied by salads. A whole lamb is tied to a spit and is then roasted perpendicular on a wood fire. The preparation lasts around 5 hours since cooking must be constant and on a low heat.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/Shortribsphoto.jpg/230px-Shortribsphoto.jpg
